SIMPLE: coincident
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Coincident
<hw>Co*in"ci*dent</hw> <pr>(k⟦osl⟧*⟦icr⟧n"s⟦icr⟧*d⟦eit⟧nt)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>co⟦ium⟧ncident</ets>.]</ety> <def>Having
coincidence; occupying the same place; contemporaneous; concurrent; --
followed by <xex>with</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Christianity teaches nothing but what is perfectly suitable to,
and <qex>coincident</qex> with, the ruling principles of a virtuous and
well-inclined man.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Coincident</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Coincident
<hw>Co*in"ci*dent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One of two or
more coincident events; a coincidence.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Coincidents</xex> and accidents.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Froude.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Coincidental</ent>⟦br⟧
